<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Penny" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Penny,</orth> the twelfth part of a shilling: <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 1</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 3.28" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 3.28" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 28</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.74" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.5.29" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 5, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.2.39" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 2, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.91" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.252" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 252</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 34</bibl> (proverb: <emph>a friend i' the court is better than a penny in purse</emph>). <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.109" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.453" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 453</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 1, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.195" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 195</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.4.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 4, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.170" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 170</bibl>. Plur. <cit><quote>pence:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.5.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 5, 10</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.160" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 160</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 24.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.263" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 263</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.8.68" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 8, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.3.89" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 3, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 80</bibl>.<lb />== money in general: <cit><quote>her father is make her a petter p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 62</bibl></cit> (Evans' speech). <cit><quote>what p. hath Rome borne, what men provided, what munition sent, to underprop this action?</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.97" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 97</bibl></cit>.
